description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/coap/coap_client.c
Lines: 458-464

When protecting a request with OSCORE, the PIV is extracted for later response decryption:
```c
ret = oscore_option_parse(oscore_opt_buf, oscore_opt_len, &opt);
if (ret == OSCORE_OK && opt.has_piv && opt.piv_len > 0) {
    memcpy(ctx->request_piv, opt.piv, opt.piv_len);
    ctx->request_piv_len = opt.piv_len;
}
```

If oscore_option_parse fails or PIV is not present, ctx->request_piv_len remains 0. Later, oscore_unprotect_response (line 319) is called with empty PIV, which may fail or cause incorrect decryption.

The request was already protected and sent, so we cannot recover. Should fail the request earlier if PIV extraction fails.

Category: CORRECTNESS - error handling
